name: Vikas Rana
tweet: In general, any activity not involving gathering more than 5 people should qualify to be opened. We should follow that for 3 weeks and then assess.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: DAILY LIFE: Grocery stores should operate with masks and social distancing. Blue-collar jobs like cooks, maids, plumbers should resume.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: DELIVERY: Food delivery + Ecommerce deliveries should be allowed.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: TRANSPORTATION: Private vehicles can be allowed. Auto+Ola+Uber should be allowed. Buses get crowded fast and difficult to maintain social distance, it should remain closed in Phase 1.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: OFFICE: People who work in corporate are among the least affected from an economic standpoint. Among this, there‚Äôs a section of people who can work from home. Those who can‚Äôt should remain closed.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: SCHOOLS/MALLS/RESTAURANTS: Should stay closed in Phase 1 till we understand the impact of gradual relaxation.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: GATHERING: Any gathering of more than 5 people should still be avoided.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: TRAVEL: Inter-city travel should be banned. Trains, Flights, Intercity buses should be on hold. Activities within a city should function with restrictions.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: Those who cannot get the masks (due to distribution issues, shortage) should build one. Any mask is better than going out without it.  https://t.co/f4pMKntC48

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: MASKS: To begin with, masks should be mandatory for everybody outside home. Govt should make free masks available to everyone. Distribution will be key. If we can give condoms for free to control HIV/AIDS, we can do masks too!  https://t.co/PII9ZeabqD

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: As we approach the second half of lockdown, we need to think about how to deal with the situation after. India is a poor country and cannot afford to shut down completely for long. We need to open gradually. That is, a staggered approach.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: India has done well by acting early and cutting off from the world and then full internal lockdown. It‚Äôs been chaotic, but a better approach until we understand the full impact of #Coronavirus across the world.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: Like all complex problems, this presents a formidable challenge. You have to choose the less bad situation. And like many other complex situations, this also needs a tailored approach specific to India.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: Opening fully will infect a mass majority sooner or later. With India‚Äôs substandard healthcare system, again poor people will be the most adversely affected.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: With #21daylockdown, India faces a peculiar situation. If full lockdown is continued, this will hamper the economy in a big way. Informal economy is hit hardest. Informal economy employs the poor and they are having a hard time just surviving.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: In general, any activity not involving gathering more than 5 people should qualify to be opened. We should follow that for 3 weeks and then assess.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: DAILY LIFE: Grocery stores should operate with masks and social distancing. Blue-collar jobs like cooks, maids, plumbers should resume.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: DELIVERY: Food delivery + Ecommerce deliveries should be allowed.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: TRANSPORTATION: Private vehicles can be allowed. Auto+Ola+Uber should be allowed. Buses get crowded fast and difficult to maintain social distance, it should remain closed in Phase 1.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: OFFICE: People who work in corporate are among the least affected from an economic standpoint. Among this, there‚Äôs a section of people who can work from home. Those who can‚Äôt should remain closed.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: SCHOOLS/MALLS/RESTAURANTS: Should stay closed in Phase 1 till we understand the impact of gradual relaxation.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: GATHERING: Any gathering of more than 5 people should still be avoided.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: TRAVEL: Inter-city travel should be banned. Trains, Flights, Intercity buses should be on hold. Activities within a city should function with restrictions.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: Those who cannot get the masks (due to distribution issues, shortage) should build one. Any mask is better than going out without it.  https://t.co/f4pMKntC48

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: MASKS: To begin with, masks should be mandatory for everybody outside home. Govt should make free masks available to everyone. Distribution will be key. If we can give condoms for free to control HIV/AIDS, we can do masks too!  https://t.co/PII9ZeabqD

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: As we approach the second half of lockdown, we need to think about how to deal with the situation after. India is a poor country and cannot afford to shut down completely for long. We need to open gradually. That is, a staggered approach.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: India has done well by acting early and cutting off from the world and then full internal lockdown. It‚Äôs been chaotic, but a better approach until we understand the full impact of #Coronavirus across the world.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: Like all complex problems, this presents a formidable challenge. You have to choose the less bad situation. And like many other complex situations, this also needs a tailored approach specific to India.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: Opening fully will infect a mass majority sooner or later. With India‚Äôs substandard healthcare system, again poor people will be the most adversely affected.

name: Vikas Rana
tweet: With #21daylockdown, India faces a peculiar situation. If full lockdown is continued, this will hamper the economy in a big way. Informal economy is hit hardest. Informal economy employs the poor and they are having a hard time just surviving.
